    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In Christi nomine. Die veneris qui fuit secundo die intrante mense iunii.
                        Qualiter <rs key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines">bonorum virorum</rs> presentia
                        nomina quorum hic inferius scripta inventur. De lite et altercatione <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terrę</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions" ref="#places/4186">Carezetulo</placeName>, quę
                        olim fuit <persName><name ref="Albertus/Casalealti"
                            >Alberti</name></persName>
                        <placeName ref="#places/2963">Casalealti</placeName> et <rs
                            key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Priors" ref="#juridical_persons/2001">Sancti
                            Benedicti</orgName> dedit, et de quadam parte terrę <persName><name
                                ref="Albertus/Azonis/Henrici">Albertus Azonis
                            Henrici</name></persName> litem movebat et faciebat monasterio Sancti
                        Benedicti. Sic diffinita est, quod ipse Albertus Azonis Henrici finem et
                        transactionem fecit in manibus domni <persName key="#Priors"
                            ref="#people/3746">Rodulfi</persName>, <rs key="#Priors">prioris</rs>
                        Sancti Benedicti, presente domno <persName key="#Priors" ref="#people/3717"
                            >Adamo</persName>, priore <orgName key="#Priors"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2416">Sancti Martini</orgName>, et domno
                                <persName><name ref="Raginaldus">Rainaldo</name></persName>, de
                        supradicta parte terrę unde litem monasterio Sancti Benedicti faciebat, et
                        XX solidos Mediolanenses inde accepit et habuit. Sic vero finis et
                        transactio facta est, quod nec per se, nec per suos heredes, nec per aliquam
                        submissam personam molestare debet predictum monasterium de predicta terra.
                        Si molestaverit et finem firmum omni tempore et transactionem non tenuerit,
                        quod componere et dare debet nomine penę <rs key="#Penalty">XX libras
                            Lucenses</rs>; soluta vero pena, taciti et contempti omni tempore
                        permanere debet. Hoc actum est in <rs key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/1426">Sancti
                            Petri</orgName>, ante <rs key="#Altars">altare Sancti Marci</rs>. In
                        millesimo centesimo quinquagesimo, indictione tertiadecima. Isti homines ibi
                        interfuerunt: <persName key="#Witness #Boni_viri/boni_homines"><name
                                ref="Sigefredus/de Sancta Agata">Siginfredus</name></persName> de
                        Sancta Agathę, <persName key="#Witness #Boni_viri/boni_homines"><name
                                ref="Albertus/de Obizo">Albertus</name></persName> de
                                <persName><name ref="Obizo">Obizo</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Boni_viri/boni_homines"><name ref="Arnaldus"
                                >Arnaldus</name></persName> de <persName><name ref="Bernardus/Sacco"
                                >Bernardo Scazo</name></persName>, qui rogati sunt <rs
                            key="#Witness">testes</rs>. (SN) Ego <persName ref="#people/3720"
                            >Albertus Castellanus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> sacri palatii his interfui et rogatus hoc
                            <rs key="#Judicial_breve">breve</rs>
                        <rs key="#Writer">scripsi</rs>. </ab>
